lead_paragraph: Although driving bans were in effect and transit was suspended, the dire warnings that it could be one of the worst blizzards in the city’s history failed to materialize.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Jess Bidgood, Matt Flegenheimer, Lisa W. Foderaro, Dan Glaun, Michael M. Grynbaum, Kristin Hussey, Amisha Padnani, Nate Schweber and Katharine Q. Seelye.
byline.original: By MARC SANTORA and EMMA G. FITZSIMMONS

headline.main: New York City Is Spared the Worst Effects of Snowstorm
